library(dplyr)
library(knitr)
library(questionr)
## Warning: package 'questionr' was built under R version 4.0.5
main <- read.csv("COVID_Main.csv")

race <- read.csv("COVID_Race.csv")
main.total = main %>% filter(main$State == "United States" & main$Group == "By Total" & main$Sex == "All Sexes")
table((main %>% filter(main$State == "United States" & main$Group == "By Total" & main$Sex == "All Sexes"))$Age.Group)
## 
##        0-17 years         1-4 years       15-24 years       18-29 years 
##                 1                 1                 1                 1 
##       25-34 years       30-39 years       35-44 years       40-49 years 
##                 1                 1                 1                 1 
##       45-54 years        5-14 years       50-64 years       55-64 years 
##                 1                 1                 1                 1 
##       65-74 years       75-84 years 85 years and over          All Ages 
##                 1                 1                 1                 1 
##      Under 1 year 
##                 1
ggplot(data=main.total, aes(x = Total.Deaths, y = Age.Group)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity")

qplot(Total.Deaths, data = main.total, facets = ~Age.Group, bins = 20) + coord_flip()

main.age = main %>% filter(State == "United States" & Group == "By Total" & Sex != "All Sexes" & Age.Group != "All Ages") %>% 
  group_by(Sex) %>% 
  count(COVID.19.Deaths,Pneumonia.Deaths,Influenza.Deaths, Total.Deaths, Age.Group) %>% 
  mutate(Total.td = sum(Total.Deaths),
         Total.19 = sum(COVID.19.Deaths),
         Total.Pn = sum(Pneumonia.Deaths),
         Total.In = sum(Influenza.Deaths))
ggplot(main.age, aes(Age.Group, Total.Deaths/Total.td, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "Age", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for total deaths") 

ggplot(main.age, aes(Age.Group, COVID.19.Deaths/Total.19, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "Age", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for COVID-19 deaths") 

ggplot(main.age, aes(Age.Group, Pneumonia.Deaths/Total.Pn, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "Age", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for Pneumonia deaths") 

ggplot(main.age, aes(Age.Group, Influenza.Deaths/Total.In, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "Age", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for Influenza deaths") 

vaccine <- read.csv("vaccine.csv")
main.state = main %>% filter(Age.Group == "All Ages" & Group == "By Total" & Sex != "All Sexes" & State != "United States") %>% 
  group_by(Sex) %>% 
  count(COVID.19.Deaths,Pneumonia.Deaths,Influenza.Deaths, Total.Deaths, State) %>% 
  mutate(Total.td = sum(Total.Deaths),
         Total.19 = sum(COVID.19.Deaths),
         Total.Pn = sum(Pneumonia.Deaths),
         Total.In = sum(Influenza.Deaths))
ggplot(main.state, aes(State, Total.Deaths/Total.td, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "State", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for total deaths") 

ggplot(main.state, aes(State, COVID.19.Deaths/Total.19, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "State", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for COVID-19 deaths") 

ggplot(main.state, aes(State, Pneumonia.Deaths/Total.Pn, fill = Sex)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "State", y = "Percent of Population", fill = "Sex", title = "Population Pyramid for Pneumonia deaths") 

vaccine$X1st.Dose.Allocations <- as.numeric(gsub(",","",vaccine$X1st.Dose.Allocations))
vaccine$X2nd.Dose.Allocations <- as.numeric(gsub(",","",vaccine$X2nd.Dose.Allocations))
vaccine$Jurisdiction <- as.character(vaccine$Jurisdiction)
vaccine.total = vaccine %>%
  mutate(Total.Dose = X1st.Dose.Allocations + X2nd.Dose.Allocations) %>%
  group_by(Jurisdiction) %>%
  summarize(Total.Dose = sum(Total.Dose, na.rm = TRUE))
ggplot(vaccine.total, aes(Jurisdiction, Total.Dose)) + geom_col() + 
  coord_flip() + scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(x = "Jurisdiction", y = "Total Number of Doses", title = "COVID-19 Vaccine Distribution Allocations by Jurisdiction")
